1
00:00:06,140 --> 00:00:08,540
=Fireworks=

2
00:00:08,540 --> 00:00:10,860
=Episode 5=

3
00:00:11,320 --> 00:00:12,119
Medicine...

4
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:15,679
Medicine...

5
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:19,600
Medicine...

6
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,679
Wenjun...

7
00:00:26,679 --> 00:00:27,280
Wen...

8
00:00:27,719 --> 00:00:30,160
Fire!

9
00:00:30,559 --> 00:00:32,920
Fire at No. 1 Noding Street!
Send help now!

10
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:35,759
The doors are jammed!

11
00:00:35,759 --> 00:00:36,799
Mr. Qiao is still inside!

12
00:00:38,159 --> 00:00:39,920
Grandpa, I'm back!

13
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:41,920
Qiao Nian, you really came back.

14
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:43,399
Save Grandpa first!

15
00:00:44,119 --> 00:00:47,119
- Grandpa!
- Grandpa!

16
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:50,640
Grandpa!

17
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:52,000
Zechen...

18
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:54,159
Grandpa, come on. We have to go!

19
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:55,479
Don't mind me.

20
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,280
Just go. Now.

21
00:00:57,560 --> 00:01:00,640
Grandpa, it's me. It's Nian.

22
00:01:03,119 --> 00:01:04,040
You...

23
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:05,680
Grandpa,

24
00:01:05,760 --> 00:01:08,079
it's me. I'm Nian.

25
00:01:09,079 --> 00:01:09,879
Nian?

26
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:12,319
I knew it.

27
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:17,519
I knew you'd been with me all along.

28
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:22,560
Nian, watch out for your aunt.

29
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:26,640
You've suffered so much all these years.

30
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:30,959
If only I'd brought you home sooner,

31
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:34,599
your father wouldn't have died.

32
00:01:35,319 --> 00:01:37,840
Your mother
wouldn't have gone missing either.

33
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:39,920
All of this

34
00:01:41,319 --> 00:01:43,760
is all because of me.

35
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:46,480
No, Grandpa. It isn't.

36
00:01:52,239 --> 00:01:53,120
Nian,

37
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:55,760
when I'm gone,

38
00:01:57,719 --> 00:02:02,120
let Laifu stay by your side.

39
00:02:02,879 --> 00:02:04,560
Don't say that, Grandpa.

40
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:07,079
You're going to be fine.
You'll live a long life.

41
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:08,360
I'm getting you out.

42
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,639
Come on, let's go.

43
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,280
Nian, run!

44
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:16,479
Grandpa!

45
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,719
Where are the share transfer papers?

46
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:40,599
Wenjun, I'm not telling you a thing.

47
00:02:49,319 --> 00:02:50,120
Dad,

48
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,520
I didn't kill you.

49
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,439
I wasn't the one who killed you.

50
00:02:59,120 --> 00:02:59,919
Medicine...

51
00:03:02,039 --> 00:03:02,840
Wenjun...

52
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:04,840
It's not my fault.

53
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,360
I did nothing wrong!

54
00:03:07,599 --> 00:03:08,400
It was you!

55
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:12,080
You were the one who abandoned me.

56
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:14,719
All I ever wanted

57
00:03:14,719 --> 00:03:17,599
was a father's love.

58
00:03:20,439 --> 00:03:21,439
Mom.

59
00:03:23,599 --> 00:03:25,960
Your hand is bleeding.

60
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,719
Qiao Nian, it was you!

61
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,960
You killed Dad!

62
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,400
You killed him!

63
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,240
Qiao Nian!

64
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,000
I'm Yiran.

65
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,120
Yiran...

66
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:09,240
Why can't you ever make me proud?

67
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,360
Why?

68
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,039
Why can you never beat Qiao Nian?

69
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:18,800
Why can you never earn
your grandpa's approval?

70
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:21,360
No, Mom.

71
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:23,439
Mom, I can help you. I really can.

72
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:28,480
From the day you were born,
I gave you everything.

73
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:30,360
Everything revolved around you.

74
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:33,639
All so you could stand
above everyone else.

75
00:04:34,879 --> 00:04:37,199
A woman like me

76
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,839
should never have had a weakness.

77
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,480
But that weakness was you.

78
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,199
You ruined my life!

79
00:04:45,839 --> 00:04:46,800
I'm sorry, Mom.

80
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,240
Mom, I'm sorry.

81
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,399
Why?

82
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:00,560
Why did it have to be you?

83
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:03,079
Mom, please. I'll do better. I swear.

84
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:05,879
Not enough.

85
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:09,000
Still not enough.

86
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,480
Grandpa.

87
00:05:13,879 --> 00:05:14,759
Oh!

88
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:17,720
Our little boss is here.

89
00:05:17,959 --> 00:05:19,319
Nian, come here.

90
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,160
Look.

91
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,920
This little turtle is for you.

92
00:05:23,399 --> 00:05:24,480
For me?

93
00:05:24,519 --> 00:05:25,079
Yeah.

94
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,120
Will it bite me?

95
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,279
No, it won't.

96
00:05:31,279 --> 00:05:32,079
This is fun.

97
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:34,759
I knew you'd like it.

98
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:36,399
Thanks, Grandpa.

99
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:40,040
Let's call it Laifu.

100
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:44,079
Nian, I want to give you the very best.

101
00:06:02,879 --> 00:06:04,800
Missing Grandpa again?

102
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,079
He was just here.

103
00:06:10,519 --> 00:06:12,399
Ever since Grandpa came into my life,

104
00:06:13,279 --> 00:06:15,399
it felt like the rain finally stopped

105
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,879
and the sky had cleared.

106
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:21,399
What am I supposed to do, Jiang Zechen?

107
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,759
I'll never see him again.

108
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:35,820
(Qiao Group)

109
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,600
Thank you,

110
00:06:38,639 --> 00:06:40,399
shareholders and members of the press,

111
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:41,959
for coming today.

112
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:44,680
It pains me

113
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,600
to share this news.

114
00:06:47,279 --> 00:06:48,240
My father,

115
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:51,600
Mr. Qiao Qibang, founder of Qiao Group,

116
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:54,639
unexpectedly passed away last night.

117
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,439
(If it weren't for Qiao Nian,)

118
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:01,759
(Song Che, CEO of Song Group)
(I'd never work with an evil like her.)

119
00:07:03,399 --> 00:07:07,519
My father devoted his entire life
to Qiao Group.

120
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:10,759
His passing is a tremendous loss
to the company.

121
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:14,879
But the company can't stop
because of one man's death.

122
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,439
- (Qiao Wenjun,)
- So today,

123
00:07:16,439 --> 00:07:17,639
(let's see how much longer
you can keep this up.)

124
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:18,560
I'm announcing

125
00:07:19,759 --> 00:07:24,160
that I'll take over
as chair of Qiao Group

126
00:07:24,399 --> 00:07:27,639
and lead the company
into its next chapter.

127
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,600
Shameless.

128
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,439
Ms. Qiao.

129
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:34,920
The former chairman just passed away.

130
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:38,519
And you're already announcing
your succession?

131
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,680
Don't you think that's a bit too soon?

132
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:44,360
How do you prove this isn't a power grab

133
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,240
but genuinely for the company?

134
00:07:47,759 --> 00:07:50,040
I understand your concern.

135
00:07:50,759 --> 00:07:53,199
I'm stepping in to ensure
a smooth transition

136
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:56,319
and prevent chaos from a power vacuum.

137
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,240
That's what my father wanted.

138
00:07:58,759 --> 00:07:59,839
As far as I know,

139
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:03,319
Qiao Nian is the company's
largest shareholder.

140
00:08:04,639 --> 00:08:06,319
Until she gets here,

141
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,560
you have no right to inherit anything.

142
00:08:10,639 --> 00:08:12,519
(What exactly is he up to now?)

143
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,639
Before my father passed,

144
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:19,160
he transferred his shares to me.

145
00:08:19,399 --> 00:08:22,360
I'm now the company's
largest shareholder.

146
00:08:22,759 --> 00:08:24,120
Any other questions?

147
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,720
If not,

148
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:28,079
please don't disrupt
the press conference.

149
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,879
She must've killed Grandpa.

150
00:08:31,319 --> 00:08:32,080
Next,

151
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:34,759
I'd like to announce
a strategic partnership with Song Group.

152
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:38,480
Please welcome Mr. Song Che,
heir to Song Group.

153
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,440
(It was Song Che!)

154
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:47,990
(Song Che was the one
who took Qiao Nian away.)

155
00:08:52,039 --> 00:08:53,360
So it was him.

156
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:55,320
Thank you, Ms. Qiao Wenjun,
for the invitation.

157
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,279
Song Group

158
00:08:57,279 --> 00:08:59,650
has always welcomed partnerships
with outstanding companies.

159
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,480
And Qiao Group
is clearly the right choice.

160
00:09:03,399 --> 00:09:04,279
We believe

161
00:09:05,039 --> 00:09:07,240
that by working together,

162
00:09:07,879 --> 00:09:10,159
we can build an even brighter future.

163
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,320
(So it really is you, Song Che.)

164
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:15,039
(Jiang Zechen, Qiao Nian is mine.)

165
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:27,960
Looks like our two families
are about to grow much closer.

166
00:09:28,159 --> 00:09:29,039
Of course.

167
00:09:29,879 --> 00:09:32,120
I'm sure we'll be working
very closely from now on.

168
00:09:32,519 --> 00:09:34,440
Wasn't Song Che overseas?

169
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,440
Why is he back?

170
00:09:35,759 --> 00:09:37,519
And how did he end up with Qiao Wenjun?

171
00:09:38,399 --> 00:09:40,519
Plus, how did he end up taking my body?

172
00:09:41,279 --> 00:09:42,679
What other reason could there be?

173
00:09:44,679 --> 00:09:46,360
He had a crush on you back in college.

174
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,600
I'm still new to this side
of the business.

175
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:52,039
There are still many things
I don't know.

176
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:53,840
(This Song heir isn't bad.)

177
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:56,159
Ms. Qiao, I look forward
to your guidance.

178
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:58,039
You're too kind.

179
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,159
Let's make this a win-win.

180
00:10:01,159 --> 00:10:01,960
A win-win.

181
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:06,480
Take care, Mr. Song.

182
00:10:06,639 --> 00:10:08,039
(Just wait. I'll make you mine.)

183
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,279
(Hmph.)

184
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:14,960
Let's go.

185
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,679
Let's see what he's really after.

186
00:10:29,039 --> 00:10:31,720
Long time no see, Jiang Zechen.

187
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:34,600
Care for a little ride?

188
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:39,600
My body!

189
00:10:41,399 --> 00:10:43,879
Qiao Nian!

190
00:10:52,879 --> 00:10:54,440
Hurry up!

191
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,879
(Let's see how you catch me now.)

192
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:08,799
Come on!

193
00:11:08,799 --> 00:11:09,840
He's speeding up again!

194
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,159
Can you handle this or not?

195
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:15,580
Nothing gets under a man's skin
like being told he can't.

196
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:16,879
Just watch me.

197
00:11:16,919 --> 00:11:18,159
(Today's the last day.)

198
00:11:18,279 --> 00:11:19,919
(I have to get Qiao Nian's body back.)

199
00:11:23,679 --> 00:11:24,480
Watch out!

200
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:40,650
♪So many words unsaid,
the deeper we fall, the more we fear♪

201
00:11:40,930 --> 00:11:48,530
♪Fate like a gamble,
locking us inside its game♪

202
00:11:48,580 --> 00:11:52,370
♪Hearts at play, truth and lies,
who could ever know♪

203
00:11:52,890 --> 00:11:56,170
♪Where this ends♪

204
00:11:56,170 --> 00:12:03,450
♪I try to walk away,
yet still step into the fire♪

205
00:12:03,450 --> 00:12:07,780
♪Your heartbeat pulls me under,
and I lose myself♪

206
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:10,900
♪Love turns into pain♪

207
00:12:10,970 --> 00:12:15,090
♪Words betray us
until our eyes burn red♪

208
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:18,730
♪Yet I still want you close♪

209
00:12:18,730 --> 00:12:22,900
♪Your tide breaks me,
and I fall for you again♪

210
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:26,210
♪Even if love becomes nothing♪

211
00:12:26,210 --> 00:12:30,780
♪When love and hate fade
into the crowd and the ice melts♪

212
00:12:30,780 --> 00:12:37,090
♪Does it mean we could meet again?♪

213
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:41,870
♪Your heartbeat pulls me under,
and I lose myself♪

214
00:12:41,870 --> 00:12:45,090
♪Love turns into pain♪

215
00:12:45,090 --> 00:12:49,530
♪Words betray us
until our eyes burn red♪

216
00:12:49,530 --> 00:12:52,880
♪Yet I still want you close♪

217
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:57,110
♪Your tide breaks me,
and I fall for you again♪

218
00:12:57,150 --> 00:13:00,370
♪Even if love becomes nothing♪

219
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:05,090
♪When love and hate fade
into the crowd and the ice melts♪

220
00:13:05,090 --> 00:13:12,170
♪Does it mean we could meet again?♪
